    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111F23/30</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 194]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 18</hi>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to inform you that I
                    communicated to my Government the contents of your note of April 1 in which you
                    were good enough to state the opinion of the United States Government that the
                    right to the steamship <hi rend="italic">Farn</hi> was a question for Great
                    Britain and Germany to decide and not one for the United States.</p>
                <p>In thanking you for this communication I am directed by <persName
                        corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> to state that, while His
                    Majesty’s Government do not purpose pursuing the question of the release of the
                        <hi rend="italic">Farn</hi> at the present moment, they reserve in the
                    fullest manner their rights in regard to the matter.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Ambassador: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Colville Barclay</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
